<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870506-0103 </DOCNO><HL> Triton Affiliate AcquiresCanadian Plant, Properties</HL><DD> 05/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OILTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)PETROLEUM (PET)NATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG) </IN><DATELINE> DALLAS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Triton Energy Corp. said its Australian affiliate purchased Canadian energy-producing properties and a natural gas processing plant near Calgary, Alberta, for $19.8 million.    The seller was Goliad Resources Ltd., a closely held Calgary energy concern.    Triton, an independent energy company, said its Australian affiliate, Crusader Ltd., Brisbane, purchased the properties, whose reserves are estimated at 1,470,000 barrels of oil, 800,000 barrels of natural gas liquids and 29.9 billion cubic feet of gas. Triton said it holds a 47% stake in Crusader.    The gas processing plant, which was recently completed, has a capacity of processing 12.4 million cubic feet a day and is expected to have initial gas sales of about eight million cubic feet a day, Triton said. </TEXT></DOC>